\subsection{Limitations and the ``Qubit Bottleneck''}
\label{subsec:disc_nisq}
Despite its predictive power, QuantumXCT is currently unconstrained by the qubit counts of the NISQ era. The linear scaling of the Hilbert space allows our current implementation to process whole-transcriptome gene sets---typically $N+M > 20,000$ qubits. This eliminates the need for pre-selection of genes and allows the model to utilize the high-parameter redundancy common in classical deep learning models to improve accuracy.

